<item>
 <title>PSH-16-0079 - In the Matter of Personnel Security Hearing</title>
 <link>https://energy.gov/oha/downloads/psh-16-0079-matter-personnel-security-hearing</link>
 <description>&lt;a href=&quot;/oha/downloads/psh-16-0079-matter-personnel-security-hearing&quot; class=&quot;title-link&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;PSH-16-0079 - In the Matter of Personnel Security Hearing&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;&lt;div  property=&quot;content:encoded&quot; class=&quot;field-item odd&quot;&gt; &lt;p&gt;On January 6, 2017, an Administrative Judge issued a decision restoring an individual’s access authorization. In reaching this determination, the Administrative Judge found that the individual had resolved security concerns under Criterion L regarding her failure to file Federal and State income tax returns from 2011 to 2015. The individual introduced testimony establishing that, in 2009, she moved her mother into her home in order to provide medical care. The individual also produced evidence establishing that given the requirements of her regular employment and the extra burden of caring for her mother, the individual became overwhelmed. Additional testimony established that when the individual’s mother passed away, and her brother passed away shortly thereafter, the individual became “traumatized.” The individual also presented testimony from her accountant indicating that the individual has filed all of the tax returns in question and that she was owed a refund for each of those years. The individual’s Division Leader and Manager testified as to the individual’s excellent work performance and their belief in the individual’s judgment, reliability and trustworthiness. Given the evidence before him, the Administrative Judge found that the individual’s failure to file 2011 to 2015 Federal and State tax returns was an event triggered by extraordinary circumstances not likely to be repeated. Consequently, the Administrative Judge found that the individual’s security clearance should be restored. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Richard Cronin - Administrative Judge&lt;/p&gt;
