<item>
 <title>PSH-16-0066  - In the Matter of Personnel Security Hearing</title>
 <link>https://energy.gov/oha/downloads/psh-16-0066-matter-personnel-security-hearing</link>
 <description>&lt;a href=&quot;/oha/downloads/psh-16-0066-matter-personnel-security-hearing&quot; class=&quot;title-link&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;PSH-16-0066  - In the Matter of Personnel Security Hearing&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;&lt;div  property=&quot;content:encoded&quot; class=&quot;field-item odd&quot;&gt; &lt;p&gt;On November 30, 2016, an OHA Administrative Judge issued a decision in which he concluded that an individual’s security clearance should be restored. The local security office (LSO) alleged that the individual (who has held access authorization for approximately 30 years) violated workplace rules on four occasions, had been delinquent on his home mortgage for at least five years, and had failed to honor commitments he made to DOE during personnel security interviews (PSIs) between 2011 and 2015. After examination of the record as a whole, including the testimony of all witnesses (which included two personnel security specialists), the Administrative Judge concluded: (1) each of the workplace violations occurred under unique circumstances and that such behavior was unlikely to recur; (2) the individual’s mortgage delinquencies commenced due to circumstances beyond his control (i.e., loss of income through unemployment and, subsequently, prioritizing payment of federal and state tax debt) and the individual’s continual attempts to effectuate a mortgage modification evidenced a good faith effort to resolve his mortgage delinquency; and (3) the LSO’s own documentation largely refuted the allegations that the individual had failed to honor commitments he had made during PSIs. On this basis, the Administrative Judge found that the individual had resolved all of the security concerns alleged under Criterion L.  OHA Case No. PSH-16-0066 (Wade M. Boswell) &lt;/p&gt;
 &lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field field-name-field-download-files field-type-file field-label-hidden&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;&lt;div  class=&quot;field-item odd&quot;&gt;&lt;a class=&quot;media-link-wrapper&quot; href=&quot;https://energy.gov/sites/prod/files/2016/12/f34/PSH-16-0066.pdf&quot;&gt;&lt;img typeof=&quot;foaf:Image&quot; src=&quot;/modules/file/icons/application-pdf.png&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;filename&quot;&gt;PSH-16-0066.pdf&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;filesize&quot;&gt;(208.33 KB)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
